Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Peel and chop the @onion{1} and @carrot{1} into ½cm cubes. Halve, then remove the core from the @bell pepper{1} and chop into 1cm cubes. Roughly chop the @chestnut mushrooms{75%g}. Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%can} in a #sieve{}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{½%bunch} (stalks and all). Cut the @potatoes{450%g} (no need to peel) into ½cm thick slices.

> TIP: It needs to be thin to cook properly.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} over medium heat. Add the onion and carrot and cook, stirring until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the pepper and mushrooms, along with a pinch of @salt{} and a grind of @pepper{}. Cook, still stirring, until they are also soft, ~{5%minutes}.

Next, add the lentils and @Provencal herbs{1%tsp} to the saucepan and stir well. Pour in the @water{100%ml} along with the @vegetable stock powder{1}. Add the @tomato puree{15%g}, @wholegrain mustard{½%tsp} (add less if you don't like heat!), @baby spinach{125%g} and half the parsley. Stir together, then simmer for ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: It might look like a lot of spinach initially but it will wilt down!

Transfer the lentil mixture from the saucepan into an #ovenproof dish{}. Layer the potato slices over the top.

> TIP: Don't overlap the slices too much otherwise they won't all cook at the same rate.

Drizzle with @oil{} and season with a few grinds of @black pepper{}, then pop the hotpot on the top shelf of your oven. Bake for ~{20-25%minutes}.

> TIP: The potato will sink slightly into the sauce as it cooks, this is perfectly fine!

While the hotpot is in your oven, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Once the 25 mins baking time is up, remove the hotpot from the oven and turn your #grill{} to high. Scatter the cheese over the hotpot and grill until melted, about ~{5%minutes}.

Serve the hotpot into #bowls{} and garnish with the remaining parsley. Enjoy!